   Safety Tech Proc SAFEPROCESS},
Abstract = {With the rapid growth of cyber-physical systems (CPS), the requirements
   on the security of such systems increases, since the communication
   networks between the controllers, actuators and sensors are vulnerable
   to attacks. In this paper, a detection method for cyber attacks on CPSs
   modeled by discrete event systems is proposed. Deception attacks hide
   their influence and are particular challenging to detect. Two such
   attacks are replay attack and covert attack. The modeling and detection
   of these two attack types is presented. We introduce permutation
   matrices which alter the transmitted signals to disrupt the attack and
   allow the detection. The proposed approach is illustrated by a
