Abstract = {This work focuses on control of discrete event systems (DES) in the
   presence of attacks on their inputs and outputs. We propose to model
   such attacks as nondeterministic finite state transducers (FSTs) and
   show how FSTs can be used to capture a very wide class of attacks
   including all previously considered attacks on DES, as well as
   additional attacks and attack features reported in recent security
